Description: Fragment of round handle to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine buff-brown.
Curator's comments: Name Sosikles. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), 55, 21. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0212.37.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0924)
